# RTSP/1.0 (RFC 2326, tcp:554) DESCRIBE request. Text message: request-line
# (DESCRIBE rtsp://example.com/stream RTSP/1.0) + CSeq/User-Agent/Accept headers, CRLF line endings,
# no body. The whole message is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the start line + CSeq are parsed for
# display. source: synthesized frame — the eth/ipv4/tcp headers were produced by the netkitty encoder
# (all-zero MACs, ethertype 0800, IPv4/TCP with correct length + checksums, src 192.168.1.50:41000 →
# dst 192.168.1.10:554) wrapping a real RTSP DESCRIBE request payload (a VLC/LIVE555-style client
# request). Spinning up an RTSP server for a live capture is heavier than HTTP; the payload is a
# verbatim real-world RTSP request and the L2-L4 envelope is a genuinely valid, checksummed frame.

